There once was a peculiar City of Ember, built deep beneath the ground as a refuge for mankind, and though it had provided shelter for generations, its mighty generator was failing, casting the inhabitants into ever-longer periods of darkness and fear. Resources dwindled with each passing day, and the leaders offered no hope, for the city was slowly dying. Then, two young children, Lina Mayfleet and Doon Harrow, fresh from their schooling, stumbled upon a cryptic message, hidden in an ancient box. They believed these puzzling words held the secret path to a brighter world beyond their gloomy city, and thus began their perilous quest to unravel the mystery and save their people from the encroaching gloom.
